
## 📖 Project Dictionary

| Term                         | Description                                                                                                    |
| ---------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Actual Revenue**           | The revenue generated from advertisers through Amazon Ads.                                                     |
| **Forecast Revenue**         | The expected revenue estimated during the planning process.                                                    |
| **Revenue Variance**         | Difference between Actual Revenue and Forecast Revenue.                                                        |
| **Forecast Accuracy %**      | Measures how closely actual revenue matched the forecast.                                                      |
| **Gross Profit**             | Revenue remaining after deducting advertising costs and cost of service.                                       |
| **Gross Margin %**           | Gross Profit expressed as a percentage of Actual Revenue.                                                      |
| **Quota**                    | Revenue target assigned to each sales representative.                                                          |
| **Quota Attainment %**       | Percentage of the sales quota achieved by a sales representative.                                              |
| **Productivity Score**       | Internal metric representing sales representative efficiency and performance.                                  |
| **Product Adoption Score**   | Indicates how widely an advertising product is adopted by advertisers.                                         |
| **Meetings Booked**          | Number of meetings scheduled by sales representatives with advertisers.                                        |
| **Opportunities Created**    | Qualified sales opportunities generated from meetings.                                                         |
| **Active Campaigns**         | Number of advertising campaigns currently running for an advertiser.                                           |
| **Impressions**              | Number of times advertisements were displayed to users.                                                        |
| **Clicks**                   | Number of times users clicked on advertisements.                                                               |
| **Conversions**              | Number of desired customer actions completed after clicking an advertisement (e.g., purchase, signup).         |
| **CTR (Click-Through Rate)** | Percentage of impressions that resulted in clicks.                                                             |
| **Conversion Rate %**        | Percentage of clicks that resulted in conversions.                                                             |
| **CPC (Cost Per Click)**     | Average advertising cost paid for each click.                                                                  |
| **Risk Flag**                | Business performance indicator categorizing accounts as On Track, Below Forecast, Quota Risk, or Margin Watch. |
| **Below Forecast**           | Accounts generating less revenue than forecasted.                                                              |
| **Quota Risk**               | Accounts that may prevent sales representatives from achieving their assigned quota.                           |
| **Margin Watch**             | Accounts with lower-than-expected profit margins requiring monitoring.                                         |
| **On Track**                 | Accounts performing within expected financial targets.                                                         |

